A commercial bus conveying passengers, a Toyota Sienna car laden with goods and a private vehicle have been hijacked by gunmen suspected to be kidnappers in Rivers State. It was gathered the gunmen hijacked the vehicles along Evekwu -Rumuodogo in Emohua Local Government axis of the East-West road on Wednesday night. They were said to have diverted the passengers to a nearby forest in the area. A member of a local vigilante group in the area reportedly confirmed the incident, saying the victims were kidnapped at gunpoint.   Police arrest mother of four found with suspected human…     Igbo can’t be trusted with presidency – Northern…     I’m most experienced to succeed Buhari –…   The victims were said to be returning to Port Harcourt when the gunmen ambushed them around 8pm and marched them into the nearby forest. Rivers Commissioner of Police Friday Eboka said it was not a case of hijack adding that the Police later recovered the vehicle He said: “It is not actually a case of hijack. The three vehicles are at the Rumuji police station. One of the drivers escaped. “He was even the one that informed us. The cars were abandoned. No arrest yet. But we are still working on the information we have”.